Hector Sarno https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hector_Sarno 0 Hector V. Sarno (24 April 1880 – 16 December 1953) was an Italian-born American film actor who began in the silent era. He appeared in 183 films between 1912 and 1948. He was born in Naples, Italy and died in Pasadena, California.
